<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="basal">Basal</a> - Baseline level. For example, there might be basal <a href="#geneExpression">gene expression</a> in the absence of activators or in the presence of repressors. This is the minimum amount of <a href="#geneExpression">gene expression</a>. The basal expression level can drastically affect the performance of systems, <em>exempli gratia</em> in positive autoregulation.